cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.NA

The paper discusses sparse coding and dictionary learning, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision applications. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the Minimum Description Length (MDL) principle, which is a well-established information-theoretic approach to statistical inference, suggesting that cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses incorporating prior information in the model, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
